Package: land4health
Title: Environmental Indicators Analysis for Health Research
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Yomali", family = "Ferreyra", email = "yomali.ferreyra@upch.pe", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5184-9595")),
    person(given = "Antony", family = "Barja", email = "antony.barja@upch.pe", role = "aut", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-5921-2858")),
    person(given = "Diego", family = "Villa", role = "aut"))
Description: Provides tools for analyzing frequency-grouped, weighted, and 
    multi-source environmental indicators relevant to health research. This 
    package includes functions for calculating zonal statistics (e.g., mean, 
    maximum, minimum), integrating multi-source data, and visualizing results 
    in a format harmonized for epidemiological studies.
